 testbed was completed. The\ncalibration system yielded the pixel positions to an accuracy estimated at 4e-4\npixel. After including the pixel position information, an astrometric accuracy\nof 6e-5 pixel was obtained, for a PSF motion over more than 5 pixels. In the\nstatic mode (small jitter motion of less than 1e-3 pixel), a photon noise\nlimited precision of 3e-5 pixel was reached.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 1 Aug 2016 09:18:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-12"}
