{"id":"1608.00415","submitter":"Valery Lyubovitskij","authors":"Thomas Gutsche, Mikhail A. Ivanov, Jurgen G. Korner, Valery E.\n  Lyubovitskij","title":"Isospin-violating strong decays of scalar single-heavy tetraquarks","comments":"13 pages","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. D 94, 094012 (2016)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevD.94.094012","report-no":"MITP/16-083 (Mainz)","categories":"hep-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We present a study of the isospin-violating one-pion strong decays of single\nheavy tetraquarks $X_Q = X(s q \\bar q \\bar Q)$, $Q=c, b$, and $q=u, d$ with\nspin-parity $J^P = 0^+$. We assume that the tetraquarks have the configuration\nof a color diquark and a antidiquark. Three mechanisms of isospin violation can\ncontribute to the decay rate: (1) mixing of the $X(s u \\bar u \\bar Q)$ and $X(s\nd \\bar d \\bar Q)$ tetraquark currents, (2) an explicit $m_d-m_u$ quark mass\ndifference in the quark diagrams describing the corresponding decay transitions\nand (3) $\\pi^0-\\eta$ mixing in the final state. Our main results are: (1) It is\nquite likely that the investigated tetraquark states are isosinglet states with\na small admixture of an isotriplet component; (2) The first isospin-breaking\nmechanism affects the decay rater more significantly than the others; (3) Our\ncalculations contain a size parameter $\\Lambda_{X_Q}$, characterizing the\ndistribution of the quarks in the tetraquark state $X_Q$. Absolute decay rates\ndepend very much on the choice of $\\Lambda_{X_Q}$, varied from 1 to 2 GeV,\nreflecting the compactness of the multiquark system.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 1 Aug 2016 13:18:33 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 15 Nov 2016 20:26:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-11-16"}
